    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nVirtual text shown on two lines after delete and undo:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/35768171/509dc921-049b-455b-9958-5b01e69146c2\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Run `nvim --clean`\r\n2. Source the following file:\r\n```vim\r\ncall setline(1, ['aaa', 'bbb', 'ccc', 'ddd'])\r\nlet ns = nvim_create_namespace('')\r\ncall nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 1, 0, #{virt_text: [['foo']]})\r\n```\r\n3. Press `j`\r\n4. Press `dd`\r\n5. Press `u`\r\n6. Virtual text is shown on both line 2 and line 3\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nVirtual text is only shown on line 2, which is the behavior after pressing `<C-L>`\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nv0.10.0-dev-2294+gc0b99bb1de\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A (deletes text property with line)\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nArch Linux\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nkitty 0.31.0\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-kitty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo",
